        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 3:05PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 304 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Montross, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small trees and blow around
unsecured objects. Wind impacting handling of high profile
vehicles. Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern
Richmond and central Westmoreland Counties, including the following
locations... Lerty, Mount Holly, Stratford Hall, Currioman Landing,
Erica, and Templeman.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for east central
Virginia.</instruction>
